The ship eventually came out of the transwarp passage. The shields had 
taken a heavy beating and some parts of the hull were damaged, but 
everything was still in working condition.

Tyrael fell down on the floor, breathing loudly from the effort he had 
to make to keep stable aboard in phoenix mode. One aspect of the 
techno-organicity had both good and bad points. While making a heavy 
effort took a lot of energy, its recuperation was faster than that of 
purely technologic transformers. 

The major stood up and transformed. He looked around and saw that the 
bridge did not seem to have suffered major damages. However, the dim 
light could prove him wrong.

Tyrael: Strikers, status report, both you and the ship. I want to know 
where we are as soon as possible.

The light brightness emanating from him was getting stronger as he 
calmed down.
